<Base title="Disclosure Statement" description="Research disclosure statement of Marcel Olbert, following the NBER Research Disclosure Policy.">
  <div class="wrap-text">
    <h1 class="page-title">Disclosure Statement</h1>
    <p class="page-lede">
      Independence matters for credible research. In the interest of transparency,
      I disclose my sources of income and potential conflicts of interest.
    </p>

    <p>
      I follow the <a href="https://www.nber.org/researchdisclosurepolicy.html">NBER
      Research Disclosure Policy</a>. No relationship, other than my salary from the
      University of Mannheim and, previously, London Business School, has accounted
      for more than 10% of my income in any given year.
    </p>

    <p>
      In the past, I have received compensation for PhD-level teaching and research
      presentations at universities abroad, as well as executive-education
      compensation from my respective institution. All of this has accounted for
      less than 5% of my university-based income in any given year.
    </p>

    <p>I have nothing further to disclose.</p>
  </div>
</Base>
